        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:10PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 109 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Buckingham, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Wingina...
Gold Hill...
Centenary...
and Toga.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
